### 🔴 HYPRLAND-SPECIFIC REWRITES (13 files — actual code changes)

These files call `hyprctl` or use Hyprland's IPC socket:

#### Tier 1: Trivial (< 5 min each)

| File | Lines | Hyprland Code | Niri Replacement |
|:---|:---:|:---|:---|
| `exit.sh` | 3 | `hyprctl dispatch exit` | `niri msg action quit` |
| `focus_next_monitor.sh` | 12 | `hyprctl dispatch focusmonitor` + `hyprctl monitors -j` | `niri msg action focus-monitor-next` |
| `lock.sh` | 1 | No change needed | Already calls QuickShell directly |
| `reload.sh` | 2 | No change needed | Already uses QuickShell IPC |
| `matugen/templates/hyprland.conf.template` | 2 | Hyprland `$var = rgba()` syntax | Delete or create niri equivalent |

#### Tier 2: Moderate (15-30 min each)

| File | Lines to Change | What to Do |
|:---|:---:|:---|
| `kb_fetch.sh` | 1 line | `hyprctl devices -j` → `niri msg --json keyboard-layouts` |
| `kb_wait.sh` | 3 lines | Hyprland socket `activelayout>>` → `niri msg --json event-stream` filtered for keyboard events |
| `screenshot.sh` | 15 lines (69-83) | `hyprctl -j monitors` → `niri msg --json focused-output` for coordinate offset |
| `appLauncher.qml` | 1 line (149) | `hyprctl dispatch exec` → `Quickshell.execDetached` (already works natively!) |
| `TopBar.qml` | 1 line (1264) | `hyprctl switchxkblayout main next` → `niri msg action switch-layout next` |

#### Tier 3: Significant (1-3 hours each)

| File | Lines | Challenge |
|:---|:---:|:---|
| `workspaces.sh` | 102 | Replace `socat` on Hyprland socket + `hyprctl workspaces -j` with `niri msg --json event-stream` + workspace parsing |
| `qs_manager.sh` | 10 lines (26-34) | `hyprctl --batch "dispatch workspace N"` → `niri msg action focus-workspace N` |
| `focustime/focus_daemon.py` | 20 lines | `hyprctl activewindow -j` → `niri msg --json focused-window`; Hyprland IPC listener → Niri event-stream |
| `settings/SettingsPopup.qml` | ~30 lines | Keybinding editor uses Hyprland dispatchers list, `hyprctl dispatch submap` for passthrough. Needs Niri action equivalents |
| `monitors/MonitorPopup.qml` | ~20 lines | `hyprctl monitors -j` → `niri msg --json outputs`; `hyprctl keyword monitor` → Niri output config |
| `wallpaper/WallpaperPicker.qml` | ~5 lines | `hyprctl monitors -j` → `niri msg --json outputs` |
| `settings_watcher.sh` | 121 | Generates Hyprland `.conf` files → must generate Niri `config.kdl` sections |

