## The Exact IPC Translation Table

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┐
│ HYPRLAND (current)                  │ NIRI (target)                        │
├─────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
│ hyprctl dispatch workspace N        │ niri msg action focus-workspace N    │
│ hyprctl dispatch movetoworkspace N  │ niri msg action move-window-to-ws N  │
│ hyprctl dispatch killactive         │ niri msg action close-window         │
│ hyprctl dispatch togglefloating     │ niri msg action toggle-window-float  │
│ hyprctl dispatch exec -- CMD        │ niri msg action spawn -- CMD         │
│ hyprctl dispatch exit               │ niri msg action quit                 │
│ hyprctl dispatch focusmonitor +1    │ niri msg action focus-monitor-next   │
│ hyprctl dispatch movefocus l/r/u/d  │ niri msg action focus-column-left    │
│                                     │ niri msg action focus-column-right   │
│                                     │ niri msg action focus-window-up      │
│                                     │ niri msg action focus-window-down    │
│ hyprctl dispatch movewindow l/r/u/d │ niri msg action move-column-left     │
│ hyprctl dispatch resizeactive X Y   │ niri msg action set-column-width +X  │
│ hyprctl dispatch dpms on            │ niri msg action power-on-monitors    │
│ hyprctl switchxkblayout main next   │ niri msg action switch-layout next   │
│ hyprctl monitors -j                 │ niri msg --json outputs              │
│ hyprctl workspaces -j               │ niri msg --json workspaces           │
│ hyprctl activewindow -j             │ niri msg --json focused-window       │
│ hyprctl activeworkspace -j          │ niri msg --json focused-workspace    │
│ hyprctl devices -j                  │ niri msg --json keyboard-layouts     │
│ socat HYPRLAND_SOCKET               │ niri msg --json event-stream         │
│                                     │ (or connect to $NIRI_SOCKET)         │
│ hyprctl dispatch submap passthru    │ NOT NEEDED (Niri has no submaps,     │
│ hyprctl dispatch submap reset       │ layer-shell handles focus natively)  │
└─────────────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Workspace Strategy: Named Workspaces (Best Approach)

Niri uses dynamic workspaces by default. To preserve your current fixed 1-10 model with minimum QML changes:

```kdl
// ~/.config/niri/config.kdl
workspace "1" {}
workspace "2" {}
workspace "3" {}
workspace "4" {}
workspace "5" {}
workspace "6" {}
workspace "7" {}
workspace "8" {}
```

The `workspaces.sh` rewrite then queries `niri msg --json workspaces` which returns:
```json
[{"id": 1, "name": "1", "output": "eDP-1", "is_focused": true, "is_active": true},
 {"id": 2, "name": "2", "output": "eDP-1", "is_focused": false, "is_active": false}]
```

Map this to the same JSON format your TopBar already reads — **zero QML changes needed**.

