## Package Changes

```diff
# Remove Hyprland-specific
- hyprland
- hypridle
- hyprpolkitagent

# Add Niri-specific
+ niri
+ swayidle
+ xdg-desktop-portal-gnome  (replaces xdg-desktop-portal-hyprland)

# Keep everything else unchanged (60+ packages)
```

---

## Risk Assessment

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|:---|:---:|:---|
| QuickShell layer-shell fails on Niri | Very Low | Already proven by DankMaterialShell, Noctalia projects |
| Workspace TopBar breaks | Low | Named workspaces + same JSON format = minimal changes |
| SettingsPopup keybind editor breaks | Medium | Dispatcher concept is Hyprland-specific — simplify to command-only |
| MonitorPopup live config fails | Medium | `niri msg` doesn't have `hyprctl keyword` equivalent — must write to config.kdl + reload |
| Animations feel different | Certain | Niri has simpler compositor animations — but all QML animations are preserved |
| Lock screen doesn't work | Very Low | Uses QuickShell + ext-session-lock protocol, supported by Niri |

---

## Final Verdict

| Metric | Value |
|:---|:---|
| **Total files** | 67 |
| **Zero changes needed** | 42 (63%) |
| **Path-only changes** | 12 (18%) — automated via `sed` |
| **Actual code rewrites** | 13 (19%) |
| **Lines of code to rewrite** | ~250 out of ~15,000+ |
| **Estimated time** | **4-6 hours** for core migration |
| **Best approach** | Copy to `~/.config/niri/`, mass sed paths, rewrite 5 scripts, fix 6 QML lines |
| **Can both coexist?** | ✅ Yes — choose compositor at SDDM login |
